WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:05.272
You are listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

00:05.292 --> 00:14.326
For more information about First Baptist, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWS.org.

00:14.346 --> 00:18.672
Today's message comes from senior pastor, Dr. Bob McCartney.

00:18.692 --> 00:19.313
Hey, good morning.

00:19.353 --> 00:20.295
Really glad you're here today.

00:20.335 --> 00:24.461
Let's open our Bibles to Ecclesiastes chapter 6.

00:24.481 --> 00:30.450
I want to welcome those of you at Shepherd Campus.

00:30.850 --> 00:37.060
as well as those of you at West and our East Sanctuary and those of you who watch us online are on TV.

00:37.080 --> 00:38.842
Thanks for being here this morning.

00:38.882 --> 00:51.442
In 1963 there was a band that was touring America and they had a few days off so they were in a hotel in Clearwater Beach, Florida and the guitarist in the band was just strumming on his guitar kind of

00:51.682 --> 01:08.948
playing around and he started playing the same few chords over and over and over and he just, he really liked the way these chords kind of fit together and in a few minutes the vocalist in the group walked in and he's playing this little tune just over and over and over and he said, I just really liked this.

01:09.028 --> 01:21.266
Maybe we could write some words to go with it and the vocalist sort of starts listening and he plays it through two or three more times and the vocalist kind of starts humming along and

01:21.442 --> 01:32.814
The words just came to him, and he, as the cords began to play, he sang, I can't get no satisfaction.

01:34.336 --> 01:35.657
Now, some of you recognize that.

01:36.278 --> 01:38.601
Do you people even know who the Rolling Stones are?

01:38.841 --> 01:43.806
I mean, he hadn't even discovered America yet when they were popular.

01:43.846 --> 01:50.994
The guitarist was Keith Richard, the vocalist was Mick Jagger, and the song,

01:51.362 --> 01:58.532
though a grammatical train wreck became one of their most iconic songs.

01:58.953 --> 02:00.555
I can't get no satisfaction.

02:01.016 --> 02:02.538
And it became an anthem.

02:03.219 --> 02:07.124
I would say you could sing that song over our culture for the last 60 years.

02:07.985 --> 02:09.007
That is who we are.

02:09.648 --> 02:13.593
We are searching for satisfaction.

02:13.613 --> 02:19.922
And that is what Solomon is going to dig in for us today in this passage of scripture.

02:20.354 --> 02:35.711
We are a generation of satisfaction seekers, whether it's with gadgets or the next experience or the next promotion or the next job, or it is the next new thing that comes along.

02:36.032 --> 02:39.756
We are constantly longing for something to fill us.

02:40.397 --> 02:45.202
The truth is that for those of us in this room who have wrestled,

02:45.730 --> 02:54.623
with a thirst we can't quench, with an emptiness we can't fill, with an itch we can't scratch, Solomon is going to talk to us today.

02:55.705 --> 03:03.056
And I got a feeling that's a lot of folks who are listening today, because it is a picture of who we are.

03:03.817 --> 03:06.241
You see, this is not a modern problem.

03:07.303 --> 03:09.586
It is an ancient problem.

03:10.274 --> 03:21.385
And Solomon, even though he had all of the wealth that you could possibly imagine, and he had women galore, and he had every experience that he could possibly imagine.

03:21.825 --> 03:29.653
Solomon finds himself trying to satisfy the deepest longing of our heart.

03:30.754 --> 03:32.596
So we're to chapter six.

03:33.356 --> 03:36.540
Now, if you've looked ahead, the book has 12 chapters.

03:36.560 --> 03:39.122
So we're pretty much close to the midway point.

03:39.906 --> 03:45.833
And in many ways, what Solomon does in this chapter is something of a summary.

03:46.694 --> 03:57.186
I don't know if he knew he was halfway through what he was writing, like he had kind of planned it out, or if this is just kind of a moment when he says, let me reflect on all the things that I've talked about.

03:57.467 --> 03:59.609
So there's a little bit of repetition here.

03:59.689 --> 04:02.492
If you hear some things, you go, he kind of said that earlier.

04:03.133 --> 04:07.218
Well, yes, he did, because there's something of a, this is something of a summary.

04:07.330 --> 04:09.773
to kind of say, okay, here's where we are now.

04:10.754 --> 04:15.639
But chapter six is also a return to a theme.

04:15.739 --> 04:20.445
Last week we talked a lot about money and how that won't satisfy our souls.

04:20.545 --> 04:26.111
And in this passage, he kind of returns to this phrase that we've talked about a little bit.

04:26.231 --> 04:28.313
It's a phrase that's used 29 times in the book.

04:29.014 --> 04:30.215
And so it's really important.

04:30.796 --> 04:32.598
It's that little phrase under the sun.

04:33.239 --> 04:36.082
Let me remind you what that phrase under the sun means.

04:36.322 --> 04:38.684
It means living on a horizontal plane.

04:39.205 --> 04:41.347
It means living for the things of this earth.

04:41.447 --> 04:48.053
It means living trying to find meaning and provision and joy and security in the stuff of earth.

04:48.674 --> 04:52.757
It is the horizontal relationship, not your vertical relationship with God.

04:53.758 --> 04:57.902
And what Solomon is saying is, here is how frustrating.

04:57.962 --> 05:02.066
Here is how empty life under the sun really is.

05:03.007 --> 05:06.290
If you live for possessions, for position,

05:06.434 --> 05:08.277
for pleasure or for performance.

05:08.918 --> 05:13.244
What you are going to experience is what he experiences in this chapter.

05:13.745 --> 05:16.530
So let's move into it and talk a little bit about it.

05:16.630 --> 05:22.619
First of all, Solomon's gonna tell us that the search for satisfaction is frustrating.

05:23.440 --> 05:24.181
It's frustrating.

05:24.862 --> 05:26.545
Look at chapter six, verse one.

05:27.647 --> 05:32.374
Here is a tragedy I have observed under the sun.

05:33.155 --> 05:35.058
Now that phrase again, it's super important.

05:35.490 --> 05:38.434
and it weighs heavily on humanity.

05:39.455 --> 05:44.201
He says, this is just, I'm gonna lay out a tragedy for you.

05:44.221 --> 05:55.295
Now, before I move into the next part of this, I need to tell you something that will give you insight as we read through it into what Solomon is trying to say to us, what he's really attempting to communicate.

05:56.116 --> 06:03.986
In the ancient world, in the ancient Near East, in the Middle East, there were three markers

06:04.642 --> 06:06.805
of success and blessing.

06:07.907 --> 06:12.253
If you had these three things, you were considered to be successful or blessed by God.

06:13.215 --> 06:14.136
The first is wealth.

06:15.498 --> 06:19.184
In the ancient world, if you were wealthy, you were blessed.

06:19.204 --> 06:24.412
And now that's not, we know that that's not the sum total of blessing, but that was a marker in the ancient world.

06:24.452 --> 06:25.373
That's what people looked at.

06:25.774 --> 06:30.000
The second thing was if you had a lot of children, you were blessed.

06:31.102 --> 06:34.066
And the third thing was if you lived a long life,

06:34.754 --> 06:40.742
Those were the three markers of blessing of having a blessed life in the ancient world.

06:41.563 --> 06:44.067
But Solomon says, here's a tragedy.

06:44.768 --> 06:45.689
And here's the tragedy.

06:45.749 --> 06:46.310
Look at verse two.

06:47.711 --> 06:55.121
God gives a person riches, wealth, and honor so that he lacks nothing of all he desires for himself.

06:56.223 --> 06:58.146
But God does not allow him to enjoy them.

06:58.586 --> 07:00.529
Instead, a stranger will enjoy them.

07:01.130 --> 07:04.434
This is futile and a sickening tragedy.

07:05.730 --> 07:09.634
A man may father a hundred children and live many years.

07:10.215 --> 07:19.845
No matter how long he lives, if he is not satisfied by good things and does not even have a proper burial, I say that a stillborn child is better off than he.

07:19.905 --> 07:31.378
For he comes in futility and he goes in darkness and his name is shrouded in darkness, though a stillborn child does not see the sun, is not conscious, it has more rest than he.

07:32.514 --> 07:42.568
And if a person lives a thousand years twice, but does not experience happiness, do not both go to the same place.

07:43.550 --> 07:50.059
All of a person's labor is for his stomach, yet the appetite is never satisfied.

07:51.221 --> 08:00.274
Now Solomon gives us those three markers and he says, what if, what if you had all three

08:00.834 --> 08:03.076
but you still weren't satisfied.

08:03.957 --> 08:05.359
What if you had all three of those things?

08:05.899 --> 08:08.041
He says, what if a guy has wealth?

08:08.962 --> 08:14.327
He has riches and wealth and honor and he lacks absolutely nothing.

08:14.608 --> 08:16.690
This guy has the Midas touch.

08:17.210 --> 08:19.072
Everything he touches turns to gold.

08:20.253 --> 08:21.515
He is prosperous.

08:21.535 --> 08:26.019
He is wealthy beyond measure, but he doesn't enjoy.

08:26.079 --> 08:28.882
He's not permitted to enjoy what God has given him.

08:30.210 --> 08:32.574
We talked last week about money.

08:33.615 --> 08:43.610
And at the end of that chapter, I need to remind you of kind of where we came to, that Solomon sort of came down on the side of, it's a gift from God.

08:43.770 --> 08:44.872
Just enjoy it.

08:45.293 --> 08:53.084
It's the theology of God's material blessings as a gift from him and just live with gratitude and thanksgiving.

08:53.304 --> 08:54.326
So enjoy it.

08:54.346 --> 08:57.010
But Solomon says, what if you've got all that money and you can enjoy it?

08:57.986 --> 09:01.571
You know, there are stories from history where that is absolutely true.

09:02.492 --> 09:15.150
There was a guy named Jay Paul Getty, and Jay Paul Getty was one of the wealthiest men in the world in the middle of the last century, 1940s, 50s, and 60s.

09:15.190 --> 09:22.740
In 1966, the Guinness Book of World Records called him the wealthiest private citizen in the world.

09:23.141 --> 09:27.026
At that time, 60 years ago, he was worth 1.2

09:27.138 --> 09:28.120
billion dollars.

09:29.201 --> 09:38.736
Made us fortunate in the oil business in Bartlesville, Oklahoma, and then expanded all over the world with a global petroleum empire.

09:39.717 --> 09:42.722
But he was notoriously stingy.

09:43.664 --> 09:46.828
He was a man who was an absolute tight wad.

09:47.730 --> 09:53.258
So much so that he had a country home where people would come.

09:53.298 --> 09:55.602
His family would come and his family would bring friends.

09:56.354 --> 10:01.761
And back in those days, and some of you remember this, some of you cannot conceive of this.

10:02.662 --> 10:08.008
We only had landlines for phones, and you couldn't do anything but talk on them.

10:08.469 --> 10:08.829
That's it.

10:09.971 --> 10:13.315
Couldn't text anybody, no apps, nothing like that.

10:14.056 --> 10:19.903
And if you called anybody outside your county, it was a long distance phone call, and it cost money.

10:20.043 --> 10:22.586
So you made that phone call really fast.

10:22.606 --> 10:25.970
Well, John Paul Getty got tired of people

10:26.274 --> 10:35.687
making long-distance phone calls, his family and their friends come into his country home and make long-distance phone calls, and he installed a pay phone.

10:35.707 --> 10:38.891
This is a guy worth $1.2 billion, he installs a pay phone.

10:39.732 --> 10:47.803
In 1973, his grandson, Jay Paul Getty III, was kidnapped by the Italian mafia.

10:48.724 --> 10:51.888
They wanted $1.5 million as a ransom.

10:52.870 --> 10:53.811
He refused to pay it.

10:54.772 --> 10:56.114
For his grandson,

10:56.994 --> 11:01.061
until they cut off the boy's ear and send it to him, send it to him in a box.

11:01.121 --> 11:04.226
And he said, you'll get, then said you'll get more parts if you don't pay us.

11:05.127 --> 11:13.942
He still didn't want to pay it, but Getty's son, the boy's father, came to him and said, look dad, this is my son we're talking about.

11:14.182 --> 11:16.085
We're going to pay the ransom and get him back.

11:16.526 --> 11:23.698
And so J. Paul Getty loaned his son the $1.5 million ransom at 4% interest.

11:25.314 --> 11:31.743
This is a picture of a man who has wealth and has riches and he cannot enjoy it.

11:33.065 --> 11:33.826
Let me tell you something.

11:33.866 --> 11:35.929
When you look at people like that, don't envy them.

11:37.170 --> 11:43.599
What looks like success and blessing and prosperity and pleasure to you might be misery to them.

11:44.921 --> 11:52.291
The Bible says in Proverbs 23 verse 17, don't let your heart envy sinners instead always fear the Lord.

11:53.393 --> 11:54.354
Don't envy those kind of people.

11:55.746 --> 11:57.248
And here's what Solomon's saying to us.

11:57.268 --> 12:00.173
He says, what if you have this sign of blessing?

12:00.193 --> 12:00.814
You have wealth.

12:01.414 --> 12:05.040
The world would say, he's blessed of God, but you can't even enjoy it.

12:05.120 --> 12:05.901
Is it really a blessing?

12:07.524 --> 12:08.866
And then he says, what about children?

12:10.348 --> 12:12.671
What if a man has a hundred children?

12:13.132 --> 12:21.044
Now, in the angel world, a hundred children, I mean, you would be seen as absolutely uniquely blessed.

12:21.064 --> 12:25.170
This is why when you read the stories in the Bible of

12:25.250 --> 12:30.779
people like Abraham and Sarah and they're old and they don't have a child.

12:31.741 --> 12:37.871
Well, this is really something that weighed heavily on them in their society and in their culture.

12:38.152 --> 12:42.319
To not have a child was to be seen as not to be blessed by God.

12:42.359 --> 12:45.324
As a matter of fact, the whispers would be you were cursed.

12:46.306 --> 12:51.154
That's exactly what it would look like and what the people would say of you.

12:52.098 --> 12:56.504
And so having children is this sign of blessing.

12:57.465 --> 12:59.909
But what if you have a hundred children?

12:59.929 --> 13:05.116
He says, and yet you're not really much better off.

13:05.136 --> 13:07.099
And now, now let me say this before I go here.

13:07.980 --> 13:14.409
Solomon goes to a dark, dark place in this passage.

13:14.429 --> 13:20.818
I mean, he says to us in this passage, is he really better off than a stillborn child?

13:22.210 --> 13:23.252
Let me help you with this.

13:24.353 --> 13:34.348
Solomon is using a writing technique, a literary technique that was very common in the intro world, and we still use it today, but we just call it hyperbole.

13:35.690 --> 13:39.756
Hyperbole is exaggeration for the sake of emphasis to get your attention.

13:40.757 --> 13:47.447
And what he's doing is he's using the most extreme example that he could possibly think of.

13:48.869 --> 13:51.954
And he says, well, it's stillborn child's better off than that guy.

13:52.898 --> 13:53.719
Well, why?

13:53.779 --> 14:00.447
Well, the stillborn child never knew suffering, never knew sin, never knew pain, and went straight into the arms of God.

14:01.648 --> 14:02.669
We believe that, by the way.

14:03.750 --> 14:04.711
Let me talk to you for a minute.

14:06.453 --> 14:08.416
I'm reading this passage this week, and I'm struggling.

14:08.436 --> 14:09.096
I'm going to tell you something.

14:09.116 --> 14:13.241
I've never been more tempted to skip verses in all my life as I was these verses.

14:13.261 --> 14:15.684
I just don't want to talk about it.

14:15.704 --> 14:18.006
But God really dealt with me this week and prompted me.

14:19.428 --> 14:21.170
In the Bible, we have

14:21.282 --> 14:23.644
biblical reason, not just Bob's opinion.

14:23.985 --> 14:32.553
We have biblical reason to believe that when a child dies, that child goes straight into the arms of God.

14:35.897 --> 14:42.203
David and Bathsheba had a child and that child died as an infant.

14:43.764 --> 14:49.330
And David said, under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit, I might add,

14:50.242 --> 14:53.668
He will not return to me, but I will go to Him."

14:55.551 --> 14:56.673
I want you to know something.

14:56.693 --> 14:58.236
I want you to know something.

14:58.256 --> 15:16.146
I know when I talk to this many people, somebody, somebody at one of our campuses or here lost a child, and I'm sorry, but I want you to know something that God loves you and God loves your child.

15:17.474 --> 15:18.816
And here's what I need you to do.

15:18.976 --> 15:36.278
When you miss that child, when you weep over what might have been, which is awful, I want you to entrust that child to the only one who could possibly love them more than you.

15:37.920 --> 15:38.541
There's only one.

15:40.123 --> 15:41.304
God loves that baby.

15:42.526 --> 15:45.650
And I want you to know that God loves them.

15:46.626 --> 15:47.467
And God loves you.

15:48.829 --> 15:51.433
But Solomon says, what if you had a hundred children?

15:51.814 --> 15:53.377
But you still didn't feel blessed.

15:53.397 --> 15:54.338
Now here's what's interesting.

15:55.179 --> 15:58.144
In the Bible, children are a sign of blessing.

15:59.566 --> 16:04.354
The Bible says in Psalm 127 verse three, children are a gift of the Lord.

16:05.035 --> 16:07.318
The fruit of the womb is a reward.

16:08.520 --> 16:11.425
Children are a blessing according to the Bible.

16:12.346 --> 16:14.930
In our culture, children are a burden.

16:16.258 --> 16:18.301
That's what many people are deciding.

16:18.882 --> 16:24.732
Many people are deciding that rather than having children, what we want is freedom.

16:25.032 --> 16:29.179
Rather than having children, what we want is extra money.

16:29.459 --> 16:36.731
Rather than having children, we want to be able to travel and we want to be able to do all these, all these sort of worldly, under the sun things.

16:38.153 --> 16:43.442
And all the while, what we've decided is that,

16:44.226 --> 16:48.992
that we'd rather have a career, we'd rather have cats and have children.

16:49.012 --> 16:50.213
That's what some people have decided.

16:50.293 --> 16:59.705
Now there are people who cannot have children, and I'm gonna tell you something, I've walked this road, my wife and I've walked this road for a while, for about 17 years of our marriage, and we understand, and I pray for you.

17:00.406 --> 17:07.574
But if you've made the choice not to have children, because you wanna pursue other things, I wanna say something.

17:07.594 --> 17:08.395
And you need to hear this.

17:09.677 --> 17:11.219
That feels fine in your 20s.

17:12.500 --> 17:14.002
And in your 30s, it's all right.

17:14.754 --> 17:26.334
But in your 40s, it starts bothering you and by your 50s, it's awfully lonely with just your cats and not any children.

17:26.354 --> 17:32.224
In the Western civilization, there's something of a population collapse that's going on right now that nobody sees.

17:33.686 --> 17:36.431
New York Times did an article on this not long ago.

17:37.352 --> 17:40.818
The birth rate in the Western world, in the United States of America,

17:41.186 --> 17:43.689
has fallen 25% since 2007.

17:44.349 --> 17:46.232
And most of that is by choice.

17:46.932 --> 17:48.394
People say we're going to pursue other things.

17:49.035 --> 17:50.096
Let me explain something to you.

17:50.877 --> 17:59.026
A 1.6% birth rate per couple, a 1.6 birth rate won't even replenish the population.

17:59.907 --> 18:00.787
I mean, it takes two.

18:01.308 --> 18:02.249
Figure that out, okay?

18:02.269 --> 18:05.112
I mean, the math is real simple, but we're at 1.6.

18:06.394 --> 18:10.418
Japan is less than one, less than one.

18:10.818 --> 18:13.882
The population is collapsing in Western civilization.

18:14.563 --> 18:20.910
Now, I'm not telling you that there is a biblical mandate somehow that you have to have 100 kids.

18:20.951 --> 18:22.272
That's not what Solomon is saying.

18:23.253 --> 18:26.157
But what he is saying is, you need to view children differently.

18:26.858 --> 18:28.159
Children are a blessing.

18:28.200 --> 18:29.281
They are not a burden.

18:31.143 --> 18:33.907
Now, I'm going to caveat that with one thing.

18:35.128 --> 18:36.690
Those first six months pretty tough.

18:39.138 --> 18:43.382
That sleep deprivation is a rough deal, but it's worth it, folks.

18:43.462 --> 18:43.963
It's worth it.

18:43.983 --> 18:44.223
All right.

18:45.925 --> 18:47.246
So what if you have wealth?

18:47.427 --> 18:48.368
What if you have a hundred children?

18:48.688 --> 18:56.856
Then he says this, what if you live twice as long as the longest living man who ever lived on planet earth?

18:56.876 --> 19:01.621
He says to us, what if you live a thousand years twice?

19:01.641 --> 19:06.226
I don't know why he just didn't say 2000 years, but he says a thousand years twice.

19:07.938 --> 19:14.666
The man who lived the longest of any person who has ever lived on planet earth is a man named Methuselah.

19:15.547 --> 19:21.134
Methuselah lived before the flood, which changed everything.

19:21.855 --> 19:24.538
People before the flood lived a lot longer.

19:24.818 --> 19:26.160
The environment changed.

19:27.341 --> 19:31.186
A lot of people think that our genetics were

19:31.266 --> 19:41.619
better back earlier that there were genetic anomalies that have taken place that caused disease and those sort of things now that didn't happen back then.

19:41.659 --> 19:49.268
The gene code was much more pure and accurate, but Methuselah lived 969 years.

19:50.750 --> 19:55.216
He died, if you do the math, he died the year the flood happened.

19:55.236 --> 19:56.297
He didn't die in the flood.

19:56.577 --> 20:00.402
He died the year the flood happened.

20:00.514 --> 20:03.719
Noah's flood, the flood that flooded the entire earth, Noah and the ark.

20:03.759 --> 20:05.341
That's the story I'm talking about.

20:05.902 --> 20:07.624
But Methuselah lived 969 years.

20:08.165 --> 20:13.052
Solomon says, what if you lived twice as long as that plus some?

20:14.013 --> 20:23.927
What if you live twice as long as the longest man who ever lived and yet you're still not fulfilled and happy and satisfied?

20:24.889 --> 20:28.594
You see, what Solomon has done, I see it systematically said,

20:28.994 --> 20:32.278
what his society said brought blessing.

20:32.298 --> 20:38.367
Wealth and children and longevity really didn't do it.

20:39.548 --> 20:43.674
And then there's this verse that he comes to at verse seven.

20:43.894 --> 20:51.164
He says, all a person's labor is for his stomach, yet the appetite is never satisfied.

20:53.647 --> 20:58.674
I do not often challenge

20:58.786 --> 21:00.028
Bible translators.

21:01.389 --> 21:04.513
First of all, Bibles are translated by a team of experts.

21:06.215 --> 21:06.536
Okay?

21:07.216 --> 21:07.997
And I'm one guy.

21:09.860 --> 21:10.701
They're experts.

21:10.861 --> 21:13.104
They know more about the biblical languages than I know.

21:13.124 --> 21:15.967
They know more about Hebrew than I know.

21:17.229 --> 21:19.051
But there's something in this verse I want to show you.

21:21.034 --> 21:27.922
Solomon says, all of a person's labor is forced on, but yet the appetite, look at that word, appetite is never satisfied.

21:29.026 --> 21:32.792
In the Hebrew text, that is the word nephish.

21:34.975 --> 21:43.309
The word nephish is more commonly translated and virtually all of the places in the Old Testament, soul.

21:43.329 --> 21:49.518
I think what Solomon was saying was this, all the person's labor is for his stomach, yes.

21:50.640 --> 21:56.850
In other words, we just take it all in and yet our soul is never satisfied.

21:57.282 --> 21:59.045
You can have all the wealth in the world.

21:59.085 --> 22:01.169
You can have all the children you could possibly feed.

22:01.489 --> 22:06.097
You could live for 2,000 years and yet your soul wouldn't be satisfied.

22:06.498 --> 22:10.565
All of that stuff would just be an illusion without a reality.

22:11.487 --> 22:14.512
All of that would be impressive, but it would be empty.

22:15.334 --> 22:15.674
Empty.

22:17.317 --> 22:19.882
There's something else that we're missing.

22:22.005 --> 22:22.386
You know,

22:22.818 --> 22:26.283
I read an article not too long ago and there was this photograph that came with it.

22:26.623 --> 22:27.925
So I want to show you this photograph.

22:28.746 --> 22:39.100
This is a guy named Jonathan Carley and he is wearing the uniform of a rear admiral, that's one star, in the British Navy.

22:40.542 --> 22:46.770
And you see those 12 medals, service medals across his chest and the little flower

22:47.074 --> 22:49.758
is because it was Remembrance Day.

22:49.818 --> 22:53.463
The poppy flower is what the British wear on Remembrance Day.

22:53.503 --> 22:58.029
Now Remembrance Day in Britain is kind of a combination of Veterans Day and Memorial Day.

22:58.810 --> 23:15.892
And so they have these ceremonies, and Jonathan Carley, Rear Admiral's uniform shows up, they give him a wreath to lay on Remembrance Day at this ceremony, and he lays it, and everybody's impressed with him.

23:15.912 --> 23:17.074
And then the story came out,

23:17.250 --> 23:24.800
after he identified himself to the media and they started researching him, that Jonathan Carley is not only not a rear admiral.

23:25.781 --> 23:30.627
Jonathan Carley has never served in anybody's Army, Navy, Air Force or Marines anywhere.

23:31.428 --> 23:31.688
Nothing.

23:32.649 --> 23:36.434
He bought the uniform and the metals on Amazon.

23:40.119 --> 23:40.219
Yeah.

23:40.239 --> 23:45.746
When the police showed up because it's a crime to impersonate a serviceman in Great Britain,

23:46.690 --> 23:48.532
The police show up to arrest him.

23:48.873 --> 23:52.237
He said to them, I've been expecting you.

23:52.257 --> 23:58.965
The media interviewed his neighbors and he was telling them that he didn't tell them he was a rear admiral.

23:58.985 --> 24:02.309
What he told them was that he worked for the British Secret Service.

24:02.349 --> 24:03.170
He was a spy.

24:05.332 --> 24:06.373
Let me give you a little help for him.

24:07.515 --> 24:13.682
If anybody ever tells you they're a spy, they're probably not.

24:15.490 --> 24:21.637
This guy's probably got a mental illness or he's just a compulsive liar.

24:23.359 --> 24:29.706
But what he wants is to impress, but there's nothing behind the impression.

24:31.347 --> 24:32.829
There is emptiness there.

24:33.009 --> 24:33.950
There's nothing.

24:34.811 --> 24:36.673
And that's what Solomon is trying to get at.

24:36.713 --> 24:43.681
And this becomes so frustrating for us as we listen, as we read through this, and we're like Solomon, this is just dark and empty stuff.

24:44.041 --> 24:44.722
And he knows that.

24:46.082 --> 24:48.945
So then he gives us the satisfaction solution.

24:50.226 --> 24:51.547
So what's the answer to this?

24:52.308 --> 24:56.552
If money and children in long life don't help us out, look at verse nine.

24:58.695 --> 25:04.761
Better what the eyes see than wandering desire.

25:06.622 --> 25:11.888
Better what the eyes see than wandering desire.

25:11.908 --> 25:14.290
What your eyes see is reality.

25:15.490 --> 25:18.214
What your eyes see is the house you actually live in.

25:19.696 --> 25:22.921
Better the house you live in than daydreaming about a mansion.

25:24.063 --> 25:24.844
Wandering desire.

25:25.986 --> 25:34.118
Better the wife you have than lustfully daydreaming about one, someone else.

25:35.260 --> 25:36.802
And by the way, let me reverse that.

25:37.403 --> 25:42.290
Better the husband you have than lustfully daydreaming about somebody else.

25:45.602 --> 25:52.149
Better the job you have than constantly striving to get a little more.

25:52.690 --> 26:03.983
It's not wrong to better yourself, but if that is the consuming desire of your soul, if that's what your heart always goes to, it says something about who you are.

26:05.344 --> 26:14.034
Solomon is saying in verse nine, with that expression, better what the eyes see than wandering desire, be satisfied,

26:14.626 --> 26:15.427
with what you have.

26:16.388 --> 26:19.672
Stop chasing illusions.

26:21.774 --> 26:34.208
Our culture, and especially with the advent of like social media and those things, there are more illusions sometimes it appears to me than reality.

26:35.950 --> 26:42.578
Like I've said this before, but like reels, you know, they're entertaining and there's some cute stuff on there,

26:43.874 --> 26:47.378
There's stuff on there that just feeds your wandering desire.

26:48.840 --> 26:54.827
Like it just pulls you off after to chase something that's not reality.

26:55.708 --> 26:58.352
And it pulls you off to chase something that doesn't matter.

26:58.632 --> 27:01.816
And it pulls you away to chase something that will not satisfy your soul.

27:02.477 --> 27:05.781
So Solomon says, be content with what you have.

27:07.203 --> 27:13.330
There are two, two New Testament admonishments that I think fit here.

27:13.730 --> 27:14.531
How do you do that?

27:14.992 --> 27:18.196
How do I be content with what I have?

27:18.236 --> 27:20.780
How do I be content with what my eyes see?

27:21.300 --> 27:22.262
Number one, be thankful.

27:24.364 --> 27:24.905
Be thankful.

27:24.925 --> 27:31.014
1 Thessalonians 5, 18 says, and everything give thanks, but this is God's will for you in Christ Jesus.

27:33.096 --> 27:38.504
I have people typically, it's college and high school students come to me all the time and say, I need to know God's will.

27:38.744 --> 27:39.986
Let me tell you what God's will is.

27:41.308 --> 27:43.090
And everything give thanks.

27:43.778 --> 27:45.701
For this is God's will for you in Christ Jesus.

27:45.721 --> 27:47.964
That's God's will for your life.

27:47.984 --> 27:48.265
That's it.

27:48.926 --> 27:50.007
That's not the sum total of it.

27:50.188 --> 27:53.092
That's part of it.

27:53.112 --> 27:53.593
Give thanks.

27:53.974 --> 27:55.135
You go, Bob, you don't understand.

27:56.097 --> 27:59.622
Man, I am in this season right now and it's hard and it hurts.

28:00.383 --> 28:02.667
And I'm confused in everything.

28:02.727 --> 28:03.348
Give thanks.

28:04.970 --> 28:12.722
Because what I believe more than just about anything else in this life, the truth that I hang on to more than anything else is that this and I know

28:13.250 --> 28:19.999
that God causes all things to work together for good to those who love him and are called according to his purpose.

28:20.019 --> 28:30.772
And I don't know how he does it sometimes, and I sure don't know why he does it sometimes, but I am gonna tell you that he takes the good, the bad, and the ugly, and he works them all together.

28:30.812 --> 28:34.757
He causes them to work together for my good and his glory.

28:35.058 --> 28:38.682
And someday, even the stuff I don't understand, he's gonna let me figure it out.

28:40.344 --> 28:41.586
And if it's not in this life,

28:41.890 --> 28:46.036
Maybe it'll be when I stand before him.

28:46.056 --> 28:47.718
In everything, give things.

28:48.940 --> 28:50.282
I know your marriage is hard right now.

28:51.523 --> 28:52.865
In everything, give things.

28:52.925 --> 28:54.528
For this is God's will for you in Christ Jesus.

28:55.849 --> 28:58.193
Better what your eyes see than wandering desire.

28:59.554 --> 29:00.756
Second, be content.

29:02.278 --> 29:03.800
Be content.

29:03.820 --> 29:05.703
Philippians chapter four, verse 11.

29:06.464 --> 29:10.770
Paul writes, I have learned to be content in whatever circumstances I find myself.

29:11.042 --> 29:13.204
I know how to make do with a little.

29:13.224 --> 29:14.546
I know how to make do with a lot.

29:15.307 --> 29:21.233
In any and all circumstances, I've learned the secret of being content, whether well fed or hungry, whether in abundance or need.

29:21.594 --> 29:22.375
And here's the secret.

29:23.496 --> 29:27.540
I am able to do all things through him who strengthens me.

29:29.903 --> 29:34.848
That verse of scripture was not given to us to put on a big banner so the football team could run through it on Friday night.

29:36.811 --> 29:39.954
That verse was given to us for difficult moments.

29:40.674 --> 29:48.027
for hard times, for confusing moments in our life when we say, I don't understand what God's doing.

29:48.167 --> 29:53.777
I don't know why God's doing it, but I can do all things through Him who strengthens me.

29:55.039 --> 29:55.640
I can do that.

29:57.343 --> 30:06.098
See, Solomon is trying to help us understand that the constant chasing the wind, that's one of those phrases that he uses too.

30:07.010 --> 30:11.416
Grasping for more, grasping for something else, grasping for someone else.

30:13.058 --> 30:16.562
He says to us, it's just chasing the wind.

30:17.343 --> 30:18.204
You'll never catch it.

30:19.326 --> 30:20.928
And if you do, you'll reap a whirlwind.

30:22.149 --> 30:22.870
That's what happens.

30:24.533 --> 30:28.297
We have this idea that somehow it's, we're going to find perfection.

30:29.138 --> 30:31.762
You know, my marriage doesn't, it's not so good, but I could find a perfect one.

30:32.643 --> 30:32.843
Yeah.

30:33.865 --> 30:35.026
Unfortunately, you'll be in it.

30:42.690 --> 30:45.393
We have this, I call it the vacation illusion.

30:45.833 --> 30:47.034
It's my best illustration of it.

30:47.815 --> 30:51.439
This time of year, I start thinking about where we're going to go on vacation, you know?

30:51.459 --> 30:56.664
Start making plans and planning out a route if we're going to do a road trip, making hotel reservations.

30:57.065 --> 31:00.769
And we're going to go to this beautiful place and it's going to be perfect.

31:02.771 --> 31:07.055
And day one is great.

31:07.075 --> 31:09.778
And day two is great.

31:11.266 --> 31:13.109
But by day three, we're arguing over where to eat.

31:16.274 --> 31:19.319
And by day four or five, we all said the same thing.

31:19.399 --> 31:20.220
Everybody says the same thing.

31:21.082 --> 31:21.803
I just want to go home.

31:24.788 --> 31:27.893
Everybody says, it's the illusion of perfection.

31:27.973 --> 31:30.337
It's the illusion that this is going to satisfy me.

31:31.579 --> 31:35.044
And then Solomon comes down to it and I'm going to wrap this up and I know I do.

31:36.747 --> 31:38.770
But look at verse, skip down to verse 12.

31:40.290 --> 31:48.604
for who knows what is good for anyone in life in the few days of his feudal life that he spends like a shadow.

31:48.624 --> 31:53.552
Who can tell anyone what will happen after him under the sun?

31:55.075 --> 31:56.477
You go, Bob, that doesn't sound hopeful.

31:57.399 --> 31:58.120
Let me explain something.

31:58.721 --> 32:04.370
You read that, you heard that, like a 2026 American.

32:05.632 --> 32:06.674
Who knows?

32:07.906 --> 32:12.431
And we say that rhetorically, and what we mean is nobody knows.

32:13.313 --> 32:14.514
That's not what Solomon means.

32:15.655 --> 32:18.839
Solomon's asking you a question that you can answer.

32:19.901 --> 32:23.104
He's asking you a question that you know the answer to.

32:24.346 --> 32:25.107
Listen to it again.

32:26.849 --> 32:29.612
Who knows what is good for anyone in life?

32:31.414 --> 32:32.916
Who knows what is best for you in life?

32:35.339 --> 32:37.682
Who can tell anyone what will happen to him after?

32:38.882 --> 32:39.262
Who?

32:40.023 --> 32:40.364
Who?

32:41.906 --> 32:42.487
God.

32:42.687 --> 32:44.068
That's exactly who it is.

32:44.950 --> 32:51.578
Solomon is saying to us, the source of your real satisfaction is a relationship with God.

32:52.259 --> 32:54.522
And we know now more than Solomon did.

32:55.022 --> 32:57.926
Yes, he's the wisest man that ever lived, but you know more than he did.

32:58.527 --> 33:05.295
Because we know that that relationship only comes through a relationship with the Son of God who is Jesus Christ.

33:06.797 --> 33:07.698
That's where it comes from.

33:09.058 --> 33:14.305
Jesus is going through an area that most Jews would have avoided, an area called Samaria.

33:15.246 --> 33:20.993
And Samaria, there was this racial tension between Samaritans and Jews.

33:21.494 --> 33:23.617
They really hated one another.

33:23.637 --> 33:35.211
So Jesus is there and he comes to this well, an ancient well, and he's sitting there and this woman walks up, she's a Samaritan, he's a Jew, and he asks her to give him a drink.

33:35.492 --> 33:37.394
He didn't have anything to draw water up from the well.

33:38.306 --> 33:42.593
And she says, how is it that you, a Jew asking me, a Samaritan woman for a drink of water?

33:43.915 --> 33:50.426
And Jesus said, if you'd known who asked you, you'd give me a drink and I'd give you a drink.

33:52.670 --> 33:55.655
And she says, well, Lord, just give me this water.

33:57.458 --> 34:04.690
And he responded with these words, everyone who drinks of this water will get thirsty again.

34:04.834 --> 34:10.420
but whoever drinks from the water that I will give him will never get thirsty again.

34:10.761 --> 34:18.950
In fact, the water I will give him will become a well of water, springing up into him for eternal life.

34:20.852 --> 34:31.043
Jesus is saying, the water of this world will never satisfy your soul, but I have water that will fill the emptiness of your heart, and it is a water that will grant you eternal life.

34:31.103 --> 34:32.085
It's living water.

34:32.545 --> 34:33.426
That's what Jesus says.

34:34.914 --> 34:43.024
You need to understand that the stuff of this world is never gonna satisfy you and your wandering desire.

34:43.044 --> 34:45.346
I love that expression that Solomon used.

34:45.366 --> 34:50.172
This constant chasing, something new, something else, something more.

34:50.533 --> 34:51.574
It will not fill you.

34:53.616 --> 34:54.798
Only Jesus will.

34:58.442 --> 35:01.906
You've been listening to a message from First Baptist Church, which is not false.

35:02.242 --> 35:10.886
For more information about First Baptist, including gathering times and locations, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWF.org.

35:11.287 --> 35:12.530
We'll see you next week.

